<div id="review_2923528383" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2923528383" />
    <a title="Jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3283298-jessica"><img alt="Jessica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1572125481p2/3283298.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2923528383?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica" href="/user/show/3283298-jessica">Jessica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=24-ebooks">24-ebooks</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2923528383" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer293614496133508019">This felt a bit like watching old people flirt, tbh. Not sure if it was because I read this in German, or the fact that they didn’t switch to a first name basis until the very end but the prose felt quite formal, sometimes stuffy, often very flowery and therefore, old. <br/>Both characters were very eloquent, particularly Emmi. She was quirky and funny, sarcastic, with a very sharp tongue and the story just flew along and was very easy to read, despite what I said earlier about the prose. This, plus </span>
  <span id="freeText293614496133508019" style="display:none">This felt a bit like watching old people flirt, tbh. Not sure if it was because I read this in German, or the fact that they didn’t switch to a first name basis until the very end but the prose felt quite formal, sometimes stuffy, often very flowery and therefore, old. <br />Both characters were very eloquent, particularly Emmi. She was quirky and funny, sarcastic, with a very sharp tongue and the story just flew along and was very easy to read, despite what I said earlier about the prose. This, plus the immense curiosity to see how everything turned out (will they meet or won’t they?!) really made this an incredibly quick read. I stayed up way too late to finish this. However, I have yet to decide whether or not I’m going to pick up the sequel. I’m not sure if this can work a second time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="293614496133508019" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


