          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5204784-vonia?shelf=foreign-translated">foreign-translated</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5204784-vonia?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer754513560" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14502897004082290078">... It was an interesting premise, but extremely predictable... with an open-ended ending that really left me... wanting a lot more. It raises the questions of how love can be formed in this day &amp; age, online dating, e-mail, never meeting face-to-face. Is love more authentic this way? Less based on physical traits? More likely to last a lifetime? The potential for this book was great, but the execution failed to live up to it.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


