<div id="review_2127791710" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2127791710" />
    <a title="Justine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71147186-justine"><img alt="Justine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514980922p2/71147186.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2127791710?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Justine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Justine" href="/user/show/71147186-justine">Justine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782253157304" href="/book/show/10784505-quand-souffle-le-vent-du-nord">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71147186-justine?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71147186-justine?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2127791710" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6350135540979625306">I thought I wouldn&apos;t really like this book, as it&apos;s clearly a romance, and I don&apos;t really love this genre. But <i>Love Virtually</i> was in my TBR; it&apos;s been a long time and I decided to read some of the oldest books there! So I gave it a chance.<br/><br/>I didn&apos;t know it was epistolary. And I love this kind of novel! Moreover, it was well written, even if it was translated! <br/><br/>Then, the characters. Both Leo and Emmi are either super annoying, or super endearing! They can be sarcastic, ironic, mean, vengeful; but a</span>
  <span id="freeText6350135540979625306" style="display:none">I thought I wouldn't really like this book, as it's clearly a romance, and I don't really love this genre. But <i>Love Virtually</i> was in my TBR; it's been a long time and I decided to read some of the oldest books there! So I gave it a chance.<br /><br />I didn't know it was epistolary. And I love this kind of novel! Moreover, it was well written, even if it was translated! <br /><br />Then, the characters. Both Leo and Emmi are either super annoying, or super endearing! They can be sarcastic, ironic, mean, vengeful; but also cheesy, sensual, loving, desperate. The reader witnesses the evolution of their feelings, and it was really well made. Big clichés are put forward just to be dismantled. <br /><br />Only problem: it becomes repetitive at some point, before the novel takes a different direction. And the dates are not mentioned; there's only "Three minutes later", "Two days later", so it's quite hard to visualize the chronology. <br /><br />The ending though! I realized I loved the novel when it abruptly ended and I wanted more!! So, I'll go get the second book as soon as possible! </span>
  <a data-text-id="6350135540979625306" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


