<div id="review_4009464486" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4009464486" />
    <a title="Rae" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35995783-rae"><img alt="Rae" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1636047474p2/35995783.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4009464486?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rae" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rae" href="/user/show/35995783-rae">Rae</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781402786747" href="/book/show/9745480-love-virtually">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4009464486" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11225204393075113262">A lot of people have described Love Virtually as a light and fun read... That was not my experience. It was easy to read but I became way too emotionally invested!<br/><br/>Love Virtually was a hugely frustrating, highly intense, full blown love affair by email that had me up until 4 in the morning desperately trying to find out how it ended.<br/><br/>It didn&apos;t end. There&apos;s a sequel.</span>
  <span id="freeText11225204393075113262" style="display:none">A lot of people have described Love Virtually as a light and fun read... That was not my experience. It was easy to read but I became way too emotionally invested!<br /><br />Love Virtually was a hugely frustrating, highly intense, full blown love affair by email that had me up until 4 in the morning desperately trying to find out how it ended.<br /><br />It didn't end. There's a sequel.</span>
